metadata.name: Wolf
metadata.description:
Mortal Beast - Wolf

In most Native American cultures, wolves are seen as sacred symbols of courage, strength, and loyalty.

On the other side of the world, in traditional Chinese culture, wolves represent cunning creatures who embody cruelty, greed, and hypocrisy.

What do wolves mean to you?
